        <h2>ABOUT US</h2>
        <p>An artisan, traditional cider maker based in Cornwall using local hand-picked apples. </p>

        <p>Since 2012 our orchard has grown with the addition of historic apple and pear trees, such as Collogget Pippin,
            bringing rare local varieties back to the area. </p>

        <p>Our philosophy is to produce small batches of traditionally handmade Cornish cider, with a ‘proper’ bold cider
            taste with a full body you will remember. </p>

        <p>Our belief is that cider should be produced with high quality local fruit and time taken to allow the juice to
            slow ferment over the winter and spring for at least 6 months before bottling. The only addition is a small
            amount of sulphite for freshness before the golden liquid is able to condition in its own bottle for a further
            month.</p>

        <p>We continue to make our cider from the old farm house that can trace its history back to the 17th century when
            the local farmer gave cider to the workers as part-payment of their wages</p>
    </div>
