    <div class="container">
        <h2>OUR STORY</h2>
        <p>Allan’s Cider has been making cider for over 5 years, initially to use the apples dropping in our small orchard.
            There was only so many apple pies, crumbles, pickles and juice we could consume.</p>

        <p>In 2012 we bought a small hand press and bucket scratter and made the first 5 gallons of cider with guidance
            from a couple of locals and well known authors. A few months later our first efforts yielded a very dry clear
            golden cider which was nothing like the memories of the scrumpy of our youth.</p>

        <p>Over the next five years we expanded our production with the addition of a ‘proper’ press and made the
            orchard more varied with the addition of some solid old fashioned varieties such as Pig Snout, Browns and
            our local Colloggett Pippin.</p>

        <p>Our cider is refreshing and dry with a unique taste which changes with the seasons as the apples change from
            year to year. </p>

        <p>We are happy to collect apples that would otherwise go to waste and we never turn away a good apple. In the
            old country tradition of bartering we will swap some of our bottle conditioned cider for the apples we
            collect. If you can deliver to us we will give you more. </p>

        <p style="font-style:italic">   If you are interested in becoming a stockist please contact us.    </p>
